sp.p:
I think, the business before you, is to come to the Question in hand; and I
humbly beg, That for expressions on both sides, they may be wholly waved;
and if you will not speak the Question, that you would agree of it in writing.

Now the Gentleman is pleased to come to examine the presidents we
produced, and saith, he will turn our own swords into our own bowels;
and endeavors to do it thus;
